Here is a list of common English proverbs

• Actions speak louder than words. (What you do matters more than what you say.) 
• A journey of a thousand miles begins with a single step. (Great tasks start with small actions.) 
• Better late than never. (It is better to do something late than not at all.) 
• Don’t put all your eggs in one basket. (Do not risk everything on one venture.) 
• Honesty is the best policy. (Being truthful is the best approach.) 
• Practice makes perfect. (Repetition leads to improvement.) 
• Rome wasn’t built in a day. (Important work takes time.) 
• The early bird catches the worm. (Acting early brings success.) 
• Every cloud has a silver lining. (There is good in every bad situation.) 
• Look before you leap. (Think about the consequences before taking action.) 
• No pain, no gain. (You must work hard to achieve results.) 
• Time is money. (Time is a valuable resource.)
